From: 4noha
Subject: if_bwfm_sdio: numbered diagnostic printfs in attach / preinit / detach / activate
License: ISC (this patch modifies OpenBSD source and inherits ISC; see ../LICENSE-ISC)

if_bwfm_sdio: instrument attach / preinit / detach / activate with
numbered "BWFMD NN" printfs so the persistent harness log (see
harness/) can pinpoint exactly which step of the bwfm path runs (or
fails to run) across suspend / resume.

This is a diagnostic-only patch. It is NOT functional: each marker is a
`printf("BWFMD NN ...")` placed at a meaningful step boundary. Use
together with diag-suspend-verbose.diff to align the bwfm timeline with
the suspend / resume phase markers from subr_suspend.c.

Numbers are stable across the patch set so harness log greps can match
on e.g. "BWFMD 01" (match entry), "BWFMD A1" (activate QUIESCE),
"BWFMD D1" (detach entry), and so on. Do not keep this in production
kernels: every attach/resume cycle emits ~30 lines.

